What I am suggesting is to strike at the government, its military, its infrastructure and cripple it as a nation until it realizes the mistake its making, and has made for many years, by harboring terrorists within. I want to make terrorists turn from the gleaming symbol of righteousness they are now to the focus of every man, woman and child’s pain and despair. Once that happens, they won’t only have to fear us… they’ll have to fear every person in the country they live in.<br>
<br>
<font color=fff00>if you ask me, it just makes us as bad as them and the evil bastards that did this terrible thing this week.</font><br>
<br>
When was the last time anyone in the real world actually said this? Out with the Hollywood and in with the reality, g’damn! The news for the past two days, although sometimes it seems so, isn't showing you a preview for the next Arnold Schwazenegger movie. Those really are the World Trade Center builds in a smoking pile of rubble and that really is the Pentagon missing an entire section. People really are dead - a lot of people. In very basic terms, they threw the first punch and it landed soundly in the gut of America. For one, I'm tired of being hit by these insignificant little pieces of shit. I want them out, I want them removed from the equation permanently. I want pro-active anti-terrorism worldwide. If a radical group pops up in X nation they should be eliminated before they become an issue.<br>
<br>
A bullet for every demon. <p><b>Vendrix</b><br>
